WEBVTT

00:02.764 --> 00:04.157
- Hey, Garcia.

00:04.257 --> 00:05.765
- Previously on
"The Baker and the Beauty"...

00:05.865 --> 00:07.105
- Deering has
a zero tolerance policy

00:07.205 --> 00:08.827
towards violence.

00:08.927 --> 00:11.086
- And, Amy, I am forbidding you
from seeing her any more.

00:11.186 --> 00:13.574
It's time for us to expand.
This is our chance, Papi.

00:13.674 --> 00:14.914
- Asbestos?

00:15.014 --> 00:16.254
- It has to be removed.

00:16.354 --> 00:18.512
- I have prostate cancer.

00:18.612 --> 00:20.618
- So you're gonna tell Noa?
- When I'm ready.

00:20.718 --> 00:22.417
- I will be making
my acting debut

00:22.517 --> 00:24.867
in Melanie Caan's next feature.

00:24.967 --> 00:26.589
- We all know that you have
a new man in your life.

00:26.689 --> 00:28.006
I want to talk
about the interview

00:28.106 --> 00:29.767
that his ex-girlfriend
released this morning.

00:29.867 --> 00:31.987
Would you like to respond?

00:32.087 --> 00:33.518
- That publicity
is gonna be bad.

00:33.618 --> 00:35.011
That doesn't sound
like a woman

00:35.111 --> 00:36.772
who is fit to run a company,
now does it?

00:36.872 --> 00:39.031
- They're putting together
an emergency board meeting.

00:39.131 --> 00:41.902
They're gonna vote
to remove you as president.

00:42.002 --> 00:43.778
- My father's trying
to take my company from me.

00:43.878 --> 00:45.041
- Go to the press.
Tell them the truth!

00:45.141 --> 00:46.381
- I did!

00:46.481 --> 00:48.601
Everything I said
is exactly what happened.

00:48.701 --> 00:50.285
- Which one's better in bed?

00:50.385 --> 00:51.319
[dramatic music]

00:51.419 --> 00:53.333
[crowd exclaims]

00:56.357 --> 00:59.128
[soft dramatic music]

00:59.228 --> 01:05.812
♪ ♪

01:14.387 --> 01:16.301
[thuds, silverware clatters]

01:16.876 --> 01:20.412
[overlapping shouting]

01:20.512 --> 01:22.977
- Oh, that's more like it.

01:23.077 --> 01:28.336
Enough with this silence
and sad faces.

01:28.436 --> 01:30.350
Papi...

01:31.269 --> 01:33.466
[gentle guitar music]

01:33.566 --> 01:36.069
I know that six weeks
is a long time

01:36.169 --> 01:37.600
for the bakery to be closed,

01:37.700 --> 01:40.280
but at least the asbestos
is gone, no?

01:40.380 --> 01:41.543
- [quietly]
Sí, sí, sí.

01:41.643 --> 01:43.557
- Okay.

01:43.864 --> 01:47.860
And Mateo, one little meeting

01:47.960 --> 01:51.343
with one little producer
who has no soul

01:51.443 --> 01:55.248
or inner life to recognize
your amazing talent,

01:55.348 --> 01:57.277
and you want to quit?

01:57.377 --> 01:59.574
Is that the son that I raised?

01:59.674 --> 02:01.449
Someone who needs
constant validation

02:01.549 --> 02:02.981
and approval from everybody?

02:03.081 --> 02:04.091
- That's exactly
who you raised.

02:04.191 --> 02:05.239
- No, it's not!

02:05.339 --> 02:09.335
The only way to fail
in this life is to quit,

02:09.435 --> 02:11.594
and we are Garcias.

02:11.694 --> 02:15.077
We do not give up ever.

02:15.177 --> 02:17.719
[shouting in Spanish]

02:17.819 --> 02:20.437
[whining mockingly]
Ay, where's Noa?

02:20.537 --> 02:23.384
Who's Noa with?
Ay, ay, ay.

02:23.484 --> 02:26.370
Do you miss her
and care about her?

02:26.470 --> 02:28.016
Then call her and tell her.

02:28.116 --> 02:30.505
♪ ♪

02:30.605 --> 02:32.519
- Is he here?
- He's here.

02:33.361 --> 02:35.519
Noa, honey, you don't
have to see him by yourself.

02:35.619 --> 02:37.051
I can cancel my meeting.

02:37.151 --> 02:38.352
- Wait--

02:38.452 --> 02:39.883
haven't you canceled
too many times already?

02:39.983 --> 02:41.989
- If you come with me,
then it becomes business,

02:42.089 --> 02:44.898
but if I go alone, we can
keep this what this really is,

02:44.998 --> 02:46.659
which is personal.

02:46.759 --> 02:48.420
- What, no words
of wisdom for me?

02:48.520 --> 02:51.214
You can go around the table
and solve everyone's problems,

02:51.314 --> 02:54.009
but when it comes to me,
you got nothing.

02:54.109 --> 02:56.536
Do you wanna know why, Mom?
I'll tell you why.

02:56.636 --> 02:58.603
♪ ♪

02:58.703 --> 03:00.746
It's because you
are the problem.

03:00.846 --> 03:03.005
♪ ♪

03:03.105 --> 03:04.460
- Natalie.

03:04.560 --> 03:06.450
- Parents are the problem.

03:06.550 --> 03:13.058
♪ ♪

03:14.474 --> 03:15.638
- Hello, Father.

03:15.738 --> 03:20.882
♪ ♪

03:20.982 --> 03:22.490
- Hi, Bug.

03:22.590 --> 03:25.423
[music darkens]

03:26.686 --> 03:29.457
[upbeat music]

03:29.557 --> 03:32.328
♪ ♪

03:32.428 --> 03:35.199
[soft upbeat music]

03:35.299 --> 03:40.291
♪ ♪

03:40.391 --> 03:42.396
- Why are you trying
to steal my company?

03:42.496 --> 03:44.410
- Direct as ever,
that's my girl.

03:45.482 --> 03:47.640
The truth is,
I am worried about you.

03:47.740 --> 03:49.669
- A phone call
would have sufficed.

03:49.769 --> 03:50.726
- You haven't answered
a phone call of mine

03:50.803 --> 03:52.158
since you were 16.

03:52.258 --> 03:53.957
- So instead you're asking
the board to replace me?

03:54.057 --> 03:54.952
- Replace?
No.

03:55.052 --> 03:57.364
Liberate?
Yes.

03:57.464 --> 03:59.852
Noa, you've spent
your entire adult life

03:59.952 --> 04:01.383
focusing on this company.

04:01.483 --> 04:02.761
It's time you
spread your wings.

04:02.861 --> 04:05.518
You have the opportunity
to act.

04:05.618 --> 04:08.274
That's your childhood dream.

04:08.374 --> 04:11.604
You have a new relationship.

04:11.704 --> 04:13.021
I think you want to step away.

04:13.121 --> 04:13.863
You just can't see it.

04:13.963 --> 04:15.585
- [chuckles]

04:15.685 --> 04:17.691
So if I tell you you're wrong,
you'll drop the whole thing?

04:17.791 --> 04:19.528
- Every time
you have taken a leap--

04:19.628 --> 04:21.404
every single time--

04:21.504 --> 04:23.318
it is because I pushed.

04:23.418 --> 04:25.577
When you left home
and walked out at 16...

04:25.677 --> 04:26.725
- [chuckles]

04:26.825 --> 04:27.912
- When you expanded the brand--

04:28.012 --> 04:29.328
- So there's a method
to your malice?

04:29.428 --> 04:31.342
- Well, it's hard
to argue the results.

04:33.639 --> 04:35.147
- What do you want, Dad?

04:35.247 --> 04:37.635
[soft dramatic music]

04:37.735 --> 04:40.468
You definitely
don't want what's best for me

04:40.568 --> 04:42.520
'cause you don't even know
what that is.

04:44.664 --> 04:46.440
- I want to have

04:46.540 --> 04:47.665
a relationship with you.

04:47.765 --> 04:50.689
I want you to trust me,

04:50.789 --> 04:52.412
but since you are so determined

04:52.512 --> 04:54.747
to keep me out of your life...

04:54.847 --> 04:56.125
I want to protect you

04:56.225 --> 04:57.809
from yourself.

04:57.909 --> 05:00.259
You are making mistakes,

05:00.359 --> 05:02.594
and they are harming
this company

05:02.694 --> 05:03.934
and your future.

05:04.034 --> 05:07.724
Three major clients gone.

05:07.824 --> 05:10.404
Five more in jeopardy.

05:10.504 --> 05:14.729
So if you want to keep me
out of your life, that's fine,

05:14.829 --> 05:19.017
but I am going to protect you
from yourself.

05:19.117 --> 05:21.773
♪ ♪

05:21.873 --> 05:23.113
[indistinct chatter]

05:23.213 --> 05:24.491
- It just makes me so mad--

05:24.591 --> 05:26.673
this double standard
that she has for me.

05:26.773 --> 05:28.013
- That's what happens
when you're the youngest

05:28.113 --> 05:30.027
and the only girl.
- You mean the only gay girl.

05:31.214 --> 05:32.989
It wasn't like this before.

05:33.089 --> 05:34.712
I'm finally
being true to myself,

05:34.812 --> 05:36.971
and my reward is being
forbidden from seeing you?

05:37.071 --> 05:38.985
- Yeah, how's that going?

05:41.626 --> 05:44.550
- You joke, but she threatened
to homeschool me.

05:44.650 --> 05:46.809
You know, I'm the best
behaved kid she has,

05:46.909 --> 05:49.718
and I'm the only one who
suffers consequences like this.

05:49.818 --> 05:50.943
- To be fair,
I don't think

05:51.043 --> 05:52.627
your brothers
were brawlers like us.

05:52.727 --> 05:54.197
- [laughs]

05:54.297 --> 05:57.183
[punchy music]

05:57.283 --> 05:59.862
You know, if she's gonna
treat me like the bad seed,

05:59.962 --> 06:02.312
then I might as well
have some bad seed fun.

06:02.412 --> 06:04.839
- Keep talking.
- Let's ditch.

06:04.939 --> 06:06.370
- You wanna ditch?

06:06.470 --> 06:08.361
- Isn't that music festival
today at Crandon Park?

06:08.461 --> 06:10.083
- Yeah, but we don't
have tickets.

06:10.183 --> 06:11.844
- I'm sure there's tickets
available, and if not,

06:11.944 --> 06:13.873
we'll just find a scalper.
- Who are you?

06:13.973 --> 06:15.749
- I don't know, but there's
about 30 seconds left

06:15.849 --> 06:17.587
of this rebellion
before I completely cave,

06:17.687 --> 06:19.271
so let's--
- Oh, it's on.

06:19.371 --> 06:20.802
- [laughs]

06:20.902 --> 06:23.711
- Hey, you.
- Welcome back.

06:23.811 --> 06:25.970
How was your trip?
- Exhausting.

06:26.070 --> 06:28.061
How are you?
- Hanging in there.

06:29.592 --> 06:32.439
I missed you.
- I miss you too.

06:32.539 --> 06:34.454
- You okay?

06:35.411 --> 06:37.569
- Yeah, I'll be fine.

06:37.669 --> 06:39.139
I just have
that meeting coming up,

06:39.239 --> 06:42.048
and my father
has a way of getting to me.

06:42.148 --> 06:44.062
- Hey, that's what parents do,
right?

06:45.785 --> 06:48.479
I was thinking,
if you're not too tired later,

06:48.579 --> 06:50.202
maybe we could do
something quiet.

06:50.302 --> 06:52.384
You know, eat in,
put on a movie.

06:52.484 --> 06:53.800
- Netflix and chill?

06:53.900 --> 06:55.561
[soft music]

06:55.661 --> 06:57.131
Let me see
how the meeting goes.

06:57.231 --> 06:58.930
I'll call you
when I get out, okay?

06:59.030 --> 07:01.724
And, Daniel, it's good
to hear your voice.

07:01.824 --> 07:03.179
♪ ♪

07:03.279 --> 07:05.820
- You too.
Good luck.

07:05.920 --> 07:07.849
- Thanks.

07:07.949 --> 07:11.027
♪ ♪

07:11.127 --> 07:12.941
[clattering]

07:13.041 --> 07:15.812
[jazz music]

07:15.912 --> 07:22.611
♪ ♪

07:25.405 --> 07:27.296
- Mateo, Mom is right.
You're being ridiculous.

07:27.396 --> 07:28.521
- Yeah, you know what?

07:28.621 --> 07:29.555
What's ridiculous
is acting like

07:29.655 --> 07:31.851
everything's going
all right.

07:31.951 --> 07:33.306
But the truth is
is that my manager's

07:33.406 --> 07:35.603
a real estate agent,
and my big gigs

07:35.703 --> 07:37.517
are on the Palm Beach
bar mitzvah circuit.

07:37.617 --> 07:39.469
Daniel, I'm 27 years old.

07:39.569 --> 07:40.679
Do you know how many artists
get discovered

07:40.756 --> 07:41.766
by my age or later?

07:41.866 --> 07:43.374
- That's still not
a reason to quit,

07:43.474 --> 07:45.388
especially if you love it.

07:48.910 --> 07:51.604
- Yeah, but it
doesn't love me back.

07:51.704 --> 07:53.097
The longer I go
holding out for something

07:53.197 --> 07:56.428
that's never gonna happen,
then the longer it takes me

07:56.528 --> 07:59.299
to find something else
to love,

07:59.399 --> 08:00.945
something
that can actually happen.

08:01.045 --> 08:03.510
[pounding at door]
- Miami PD!

08:03.610 --> 08:06.802
[suspenseful music]

08:06.902 --> 08:08.065
- Just don't quit
because nothing's

08:08.165 --> 08:09.749
happening right this moment.

08:09.849 --> 08:11.970
All you need is one break,
and you'll be back on track.

08:12.070 --> 08:14.956
[indistinct radio chatter]

08:15.056 --> 08:16.372
[pounding]

08:16.472 --> 08:18.707
♪ ♪

08:18.807 --> 08:20.721
[keys jingle]

08:23.171 --> 08:25.215
- Daniel Garcia.
- That's me.

08:25.315 --> 08:27.435
- Daniel Alberto Garcia,
you're under arrest

08:27.535 --> 08:29.158
for the assault and battery
of Kurt Malick.

08:29.258 --> 08:30.268
- Wait, wait, what?

08:30.368 --> 08:31.723
- You have the right
to remain silent.

08:31.823 --> 08:33.790
Anything you say
can and will be used

08:33.890 --> 08:35.244
against you in a court of law.
- Daniel--

08:35.344 --> 08:36.469
- You have the right
to an attorney.

08:36.569 --> 08:38.001
- Sir--

08:38.101 --> 08:40.015
- If you cannot afford one,
one will be assigned to you...

08:43.804 --> 08:46.576
[low, indistinct chatter]

08:46.676 --> 08:49.447
[soft dramatic music]

08:49.547 --> 08:52.624
♪ ♪

08:52.724 --> 08:54.638
- Daniel Garcia!

08:56.322 --> 08:57.792
- How could this have
happened?

08:57.892 --> 08:59.629
- The press just
ambushed me.

08:59.729 --> 09:01.237
There was this one
that was harassing me, and I--

09:01.337 --> 09:02.577
- So you punched him?

09:02.677 --> 09:05.065
Who are you and what
have you done with my son?

09:05.165 --> 09:07.745
- I'm sorry.
I have no excuse.

09:07.845 --> 09:09.850
- Daniel, assault
and battery is a felony.

09:09.950 --> 09:11.382
You could have a record.

09:11.482 --> 09:13.449
Do you have any idea what
that can do to your future?

09:13.549 --> 09:14.942
- Are you safe?

09:15.042 --> 09:16.932
- Yeah, I'm in a holding cell,

09:17.032 --> 09:19.076
but if I make bail today,
they'll release me,

09:19.176 --> 09:20.760
and I don't have to see
the inside of a real jail.

09:20.860 --> 09:22.774
- How much is bail?

09:23.387 --> 09:24.627
- $10,000.

09:24.727 --> 09:25.890
- $10,000?
[screams in Spanish]

09:25.990 --> 09:27.881
- But you only have to come up
with $1,000 of that.

09:27.981 --> 09:29.182
- Oh.
[laughs]

09:29.282 --> 09:30.943
Only 1,000--
let me go check my purse.

09:31.043 --> 09:32.819
[speaking Spanish]

09:32.919 --> 09:34.312
- All right, all right,
listen, listen.

09:34.412 --> 09:36.226
We'll go and work
on the bail, all right?

09:36.326 --> 09:39.441
You, stay safe, okay?

09:39.541 --> 09:41.738
[punchy Latin pop music]

09:41.838 --> 09:44.112
- [singing in Spanish]

09:44.212 --> 09:46.409
♪ ♪

09:46.509 --> 09:48.820
- Daniel has
his "Food Diaries,"

09:48.920 --> 09:50.351
so these are

09:50.451 --> 09:52.151
Natalie's "Rebellion Diaries."

09:52.251 --> 09:53.758
Entry one--

09:53.858 --> 09:57.510
Amy and I are currently
shopping for some snacks

09:57.610 --> 10:00.458
because food at these concerts
costs, like, a zillion dollars.

10:00.558 --> 10:02.793
I say that like I've
ever been to one though.

10:02.893 --> 10:04.171
- Nevertheless, you are right.

10:04.271 --> 10:05.549
- [chuckles]

10:05.649 --> 10:07.386
We're getting a bunch
of junk food

10:07.486 --> 10:09.760
because all great rebellions
are fueled

10:09.860 --> 10:12.363
off sugar and caffeine.

10:12.463 --> 10:13.320
[laughter]

10:13.420 --> 10:14.698
♪ ♪

10:14.798 --> 10:16.689
- Ah, anything else?
- What else do you want?

10:16.789 --> 10:17.646
- I don't know.

10:17.746 --> 10:19.292
♪ ♪

10:19.392 --> 10:22.201
It's so funny.
It's like we could do anything.

10:22.301 --> 10:24.153
We could go anywhere.

10:24.253 --> 10:26.603
It's like
you don't even realize

10:26.703 --> 10:28.732
you're living on autopilot
until you break the mold.

10:29.996 --> 10:32.154
- You can take the girl
out of the philosophy class--

10:32.254 --> 10:33.800
[laughter]

10:33.900 --> 10:35.523
- Sorry, am I being
a total buzzkill?

10:35.623 --> 10:36.786
- Um, no, the opposite.

10:36.886 --> 10:38.853
[both chuckle]

10:38.953 --> 10:40.346
But I do think
you're missing something

10:40.446 --> 10:41.609
that all great rebels
should have.

10:41.709 --> 10:43.217
- Charisma?
Courage?

10:43.317 --> 10:45.361
♪ ♪

10:45.461 --> 10:47.237
- Colored hair.

10:47.337 --> 10:49.036
I love the purple.
- Yeah.

10:49.136 --> 10:51.295
The green looks good too.
- Thanks.

10:51.395 --> 10:53.094
Happy?
- [sighs]

10:53.194 --> 10:54.434
It's not even lunch
yet, and, already,

10:54.534 --> 10:55.850
this is the best day
of my life.

10:55.950 --> 10:56.807
- Yes.

10:56.907 --> 10:57.764
[laughter]

10:57.864 --> 11:00.826
♪ ♪

11:00.926 --> 11:03.162
Miami Mayhem here we come.
- Whoo!

11:03.262 --> 11:04.157
- [laughs]

11:04.257 --> 11:08.636
♪ ♪

11:08.736 --> 11:09.593
[paper slams]

11:09.693 --> 11:11.009
- We gotta get a bail bondsman.

11:11.109 --> 11:12.655
- Our credit is maxed out.

11:12.755 --> 11:14.301
If we get a loan
from a bondsman,

11:14.401 --> 11:15.526
how are we gonna repay it?

11:15.626 --> 11:17.364
- It's either that
or we're gonna have to use

11:17.464 --> 11:19.508
Natalie's quinceañera money
like I said before.

11:19.608 --> 11:21.345
- No, it is not fair
for Natalie to have to pay

11:21.445 --> 11:22.340
for Daniel's problems.

11:22.440 --> 11:23.948
- Well, someone
in this family has to.

11:24.048 --> 11:25.594
- I'm gonna pawn my equipment.

11:25.694 --> 11:26.781
- Mateo--

11:26.881 --> 11:28.159
- It won't be as much
as it would

11:28.259 --> 11:29.499
if I were to straight up
sell it,

11:29.599 --> 11:31.681
but we need the money now
before they transfer Daniel

11:31.781 --> 11:33.480
to someplace
where they shave his head

11:33.580 --> 11:34.743
and give him a teardrop tattoo.

11:34.843 --> 11:37.385
Have you guys ever
seen the show "Oz"?

11:37.485 --> 11:39.399
You know what happens
in that show?

11:40.471 --> 11:42.285
Listen, it won't be
the whole grand, okay?

11:42.385 --> 11:44.299
But it's gonna be something.

11:46.863 --> 11:50.936
- Mi amor, do you realize
that, right now,

11:51.036 --> 11:52.950
you are my favorite son
in the family?

11:54.635 --> 11:56.640
- When you put it that way...

11:56.740 --> 11:58.171
it gets me scared
for all of us.

11:58.271 --> 12:01.042
[soft upbeat music]

12:01.142 --> 12:07.550
♪ ♪

12:07.650 --> 12:11.034
- My father helped me
start this business.

12:11.134 --> 12:13.139
He gave me a loan and he said,

12:13.239 --> 12:15.612
"Here, Bug, go play."

12:17.144 --> 12:18.575
And all of a sudden
I had a company...

12:18.675 --> 12:20.221
[chuckles softly]

12:20.321 --> 12:21.637
And, every day,
people would ask me,

12:21.737 --> 12:24.011
"Is this right?
Is this wrong?"

12:24.111 --> 12:25.657
And, to tell the truth,

12:25.757 --> 12:28.222
I had no business
running a company.

12:28.322 --> 12:31.629
I was just a kid,
but I knew what I wanted,

12:31.729 --> 12:34.423
and I built this brand.

12:34.523 --> 12:37.486
I felt every fabric.

12:37.586 --> 12:40.318
I approved every design,

12:40.418 --> 12:45.525
all the while asking myself,
"What do I want to say?"

12:45.625 --> 12:48.664
And as our company grew,
that became our message.

12:48.764 --> 12:52.453
We told women,
"Your voice matters."

12:52.553 --> 12:56.243
Our brand tells women
that they are capable enough

12:56.343 --> 13:01.411
and strong enough
to run their own companies.

13:01.511 --> 13:04.895
And that is why
we are successful.

13:04.995 --> 13:08.110
[thoughtful music]

13:08.210 --> 13:11.096
♪ ♪

13:11.196 --> 13:13.967
[indistinct chatter]

13:14.067 --> 13:16.341
- Daniel Garcia!

13:16.441 --> 13:18.355
You're out.

13:20.498 --> 13:22.657
[keys jingle]

13:22.757 --> 13:25.030
[indistinct PA announcements]

13:25.130 --> 13:27.044
Garcia.

13:29.150 --> 13:32.021
- Your girlfriend's over there.
Get out of here.

13:33.208 --> 13:34.677
- [sighs]

13:34.777 --> 13:37.472
♪ ♪

13:37.572 --> 13:38.812
- Vanessa.

13:38.912 --> 13:41.912
♪ ♪

13:46.415 --> 13:47.654
- You--you bailed me out?

13:47.754 --> 13:49.415
- [laughs]
No.

13:49.515 --> 13:50.564
Absolutely not.

13:50.664 --> 13:53.014
I got Kurt
to drop the complaint.

13:53.114 --> 13:55.349
It's over.
You're free.

13:55.449 --> 13:57.722
- Oh, my God.
Thank you.

13:57.822 --> 13:59.100
Thank you so much for this.

13:59.200 --> 14:01.244
- It's fine.

14:01.344 --> 14:04.077
It was the right thing to do,
but now I'm late.

14:04.177 --> 14:06.986
- Come on. I'll drive you home.
- Yeah.

14:07.086 --> 14:09.000
[phone rings]

14:09.574 --> 14:10.853
- Hello.
- Hey, it's me.

14:10.953 --> 14:12.767
- Daniel--Daniel, are you okay?

14:12.867 --> 14:14.068
We're working
on your bail right now.

14:14.168 --> 14:15.255
- We don't need it.

14:15.355 --> 14:17.360
Vanessa got Kurt
to drop the complaint.

14:17.460 --> 14:18.662
I'm a free man.

14:18.762 --> 14:20.040
- [gasps]

14:20.140 --> 14:21.418
- What?

14:21.518 --> 14:23.217
- So we don't need the bail?

14:23.317 --> 14:24.749
- And there won't
be any kind of record?

14:24.849 --> 14:26.548
- And you're with Vanessa
right now?

14:26.648 --> 14:28.385
- She's driving me home.

14:28.485 --> 14:30.031
- Are you safe?
- Yeah.

14:30.131 --> 14:31.256
- [sighs]

14:31.356 --> 14:33.821
♪ ♪

14:33.921 --> 14:35.084
- [sighs]

14:35.184 --> 14:38.262
[punchy music]

14:38.362 --> 14:39.755
What are you doing?

14:39.855 --> 14:41.898
- I have a showing
I have to make.

14:41.998 --> 14:45.076
- Whoa, whoa.
Forget--my phone's dead.

14:45.176 --> 14:46.645
We're on our way.
I'll see you guys soon.

14:46.745 --> 14:47.832
- Sounds like old times.

14:47.932 --> 14:49.746
- [speaking Spanish]
- [laughs]

14:49.846 --> 14:51.851
- Where are we going?
- A shortcut.

14:51.951 --> 14:52.808
[tires squeal]

14:52.908 --> 14:54.072
See?
That's the way out.

14:54.172 --> 14:55.679
♪ ♪

14:55.779 --> 14:57.134
- That's not an exit.
- Okay, stop.

14:57.234 --> 14:59.048
- V, I don't think that's it.
I'm just trying to help.

14:59.148 --> 15:00.962
- Well, you're not helping.
You're stressing me out.

15:01.062 --> 15:02.149
- Wait, watch out!
Wait!

15:02.249 --> 15:04.982
[tires pop, screeching]

15:05.082 --> 15:06.996
♪ ♪

15:08.986 --> 15:11.168
- Don't say a word.

15:13.389 --> 15:15.011
[hip-hop music playing
over speakers]

15:15.111 --> 15:17.155
[indistinct chatter, cheering]

15:17.255 --> 15:20.026
- [singing in Spanish]

15:20.126 --> 15:26.710
♪ ♪

15:32.185 --> 15:34.673
- Oh, my God, we should.
- Yes, yes, yes, yeah.

15:37.774 --> 15:40.966
- Feels like I'm living
on some strange, alien planet.

15:41.066 --> 15:42.841
♪ ♪

15:42.941 --> 15:44.794
There's definitely still
a skeeze factor to it though.

15:44.894 --> 15:45.751
- [laughs]

15:45.851 --> 15:47.880
- She left school grounds?

15:49.602 --> 15:51.516
And she hasn't been back?

15:52.473 --> 15:53.598
Okay.

15:53.698 --> 15:55.612
Okay, thank you.

15:56.187 --> 15:57.580
No--[chuckles awkwardly]

15:57.680 --> 15:59.594
Rest assured,
this won't happen again.

16:01.469 --> 16:03.383
Thank you.
Okay, bye-bye. Bye.

16:05.910 --> 16:06.997
- Natalie?

16:07.097 --> 16:09.011
- [speaking Spanish]

16:12.111 --> 16:13.658
No.
- Mari--

16:13.758 --> 16:15.672
- No.
- [speaks Spanish]

16:16.514 --> 16:18.060
Rafael.

16:18.160 --> 16:20.342
[keyboard clacking]

16:22.907 --> 16:24.821
- I can see
your typing's improved.

16:27.309 --> 16:28.511
- Really.

16:28.611 --> 16:30.525
- Key Biscayne?
- Mm-hmm.

16:31.099 --> 16:33.013
Where the music festival is.

16:34.659 --> 16:36.894
And how do you think
she got there?

16:36.994 --> 16:39.421
I'll give you one guess.
Amy.

16:39.521 --> 16:40.952
She's with Amy.

16:41.052 --> 16:44.282
Even though we forbid her to be
with that girl, she's with Amy.

16:44.382 --> 16:45.545
- Actually, you did.

16:45.645 --> 16:47.727
- And she thinks
she can fool me?

16:47.827 --> 16:50.790
Mira, I was the queen
of getting away with things.

16:50.890 --> 16:51.977
[speaks Spanish]

16:52.077 --> 16:54.809
- Mari, calm down, okay?

16:54.909 --> 16:58.752
We're talking about Natalie.
She's a National Merit Scholar.

16:58.852 --> 17:01.011
Do you think she doesn't know
how to turn off her phone?

17:01.111 --> 17:02.925
She wants us
to know where she is.

17:03.025 --> 17:04.456
This is her idea of rebelling--

17:04.556 --> 17:06.485
going to a concert
on a Friday afternoon.

17:06.585 --> 17:07.940
[soft dramatic music]

17:08.040 --> 17:10.160
Oye, don't you see
how lucky we are?

17:10.260 --> 17:12.648
- No, I don't see
how lucky we are.

17:12.748 --> 17:14.830
My daughter
is getting into fights.

17:14.930 --> 17:16.208
She's cutting school.

17:16.308 --> 17:18.697
- What is this about, Mari?

17:18.797 --> 17:21.338
I know this is not about
the fact that Amy is a girl

17:21.438 --> 17:23.520
because you don't have
a bigoted bone in your body.

17:23.620 --> 17:25.396
♪ ♪

17:25.496 --> 17:27.578
We're her family.

17:27.678 --> 17:30.028
If we don't protect her
and make her feel safe,

17:30.128 --> 17:34.660
she's gonna turn away from us
and find people who do.

17:34.760 --> 17:36.306
Okay?

17:36.406 --> 17:38.718
- [sniffles, sobs quietly]

17:38.818 --> 17:41.321
♪ ♪

17:41.421 --> 17:43.579
- I didn't call this meeting
here today

17:43.679 --> 17:46.412
to question
my daughter's capabilities.

17:46.512 --> 17:48.503
They are peerless.

17:51.067 --> 17:55.370
I called this meeting
because I do feel

17:55.470 --> 17:58.164
I need to question
her commitment.

17:58.264 --> 17:59.504
- I wanna talk to you
about the rumors

17:59.604 --> 18:01.150
that your next move
will be into acting.

18:01.250 --> 18:02.643
- Those rumors are true.

18:02.743 --> 18:04.825
I can confirm
that I will be playing

18:04.925 --> 18:06.663
the lead in Melanie Caan's
new feature.

18:06.763 --> 18:08.424
- That is amazing.

18:08.524 --> 18:09.802
The one shooting
in Morocco, right?

18:09.902 --> 18:10.835
- Yes.
[remote clicks]

18:10.935 --> 18:12.060
- Morocco.

18:12.160 --> 18:14.510
Shooting there
for three months acting,

18:14.610 --> 18:17.611
which is a childhood dream
of hers.

18:17.711 --> 18:20.673
♪ ♪

18:20.773 --> 18:24.234
I also called this meeting
because I feel myself

18:24.334 --> 18:27.143
compelled to question
her judgment.

18:27.243 --> 18:28.559
♪ ♪

18:28.659 --> 18:31.009
Now, we all know that Noa
has a new man in her life.

18:31.109 --> 18:34.187
After all, that is
the entire reason

18:34.287 --> 18:36.369
you are all sitting here today,

18:36.469 --> 18:39.852
but what you might not know
was that my daughter

18:39.952 --> 18:41.804
now approves of violence.

18:41.904 --> 18:44.140
♪ ♪

18:44.240 --> 18:46.819
I can assure you
that hanging out

18:46.919 --> 18:50.456
with known felons is not good
for the bottom line.

18:50.556 --> 18:57.193
♪ ♪

18:57.293 --> 18:59.414
Ladies and gentlemen...

18:59.514 --> 19:02.438
my daughter will always be
the face of this brand.

19:02.538 --> 19:05.692
That's given,
but one thing is certain.

19:05.792 --> 19:08.716
She can no longer
run this company.

19:08.816 --> 19:11.510
She must be replaced.

19:11.610 --> 19:14.099
♪ ♪

19:18.003 --> 19:19.434
- Hey, Daniel, it's me.

19:19.534 --> 19:22.076
I'm really worried about you.
Can you please call me back?

19:22.176 --> 19:23.990
- [sighs]
This is a nightmare.

19:24.090 --> 19:25.253
- Your dad was right.

19:25.353 --> 19:27.856
Daniel was arrested
for assault and battery.

19:27.956 --> 19:28.966
- [sighs]
Oh, God.

19:29.066 --> 19:31.837
[soft dramatic music]

19:31.937 --> 19:34.134
♪ ♪

19:34.234 --> 19:37.159
- I'm gonna lose this company.
My boyfriend's in jail.

19:37.259 --> 19:39.073
The press is gonna have
a field day with that.

19:39.173 --> 19:41.484
My father painted me
as distracted and disinterested

19:41.584 --> 19:43.092
in that room,
and you know what?

19:43.192 --> 19:44.202
He's right.

19:44.302 --> 19:46.116
♪ ♪

19:46.216 --> 19:48.566
I took my eye off the ball,
and now I'm gonna pay.

19:48.666 --> 19:52.394
♪ ♪

19:52.494 --> 19:53.849
- You could have gone
with the tow truck.

19:53.949 --> 19:54.921
- What was I gonna do?

19:55.021 --> 19:56.146
Leave you by the side
of the road?

19:56.246 --> 19:58.519
- Must have been tempting.

19:58.619 --> 20:00.625
- You know me better than that.

20:00.725 --> 20:02.539
- Hold on, how about
your showing?

20:02.639 --> 20:06.007
- Gone!
The minute we hit those spikes.

20:07.692 --> 20:10.027
- I'm sorry.
- That was your fault.

20:11.214 --> 20:12.453
- I feel like every time
I see you,

20:12.553 --> 20:13.985
I've got something new
to apologize for.

20:14.085 --> 20:15.478
- Yep.

20:15.578 --> 20:18.142
Our breakup is just the gift
that keeps on giving.

20:20.210 --> 20:23.057
Okay, how about this?
No more sorrys.

20:23.157 --> 20:24.665
I don't think either of us
was prepared

20:24.765 --> 20:26.081
for the Noa Hamilton hurricane.

20:26.181 --> 20:27.651
Okay?

20:27.751 --> 20:31.020
I'm not blaming her,
but, when you think about it,

20:31.120 --> 20:32.972
a good amount of the chaos
is because of who she is.

20:33.072 --> 20:34.541
I'm just saying.

20:34.641 --> 20:36.570
Like, for example,
when you break up with someone,

20:36.670 --> 20:38.216
you stalk them on Facebook.

20:38.316 --> 20:41.164
Me, I see you two
everywhere I look.

20:41.264 --> 20:43.002
- It's been a challenge
for the whole family.

20:43.102 --> 20:45.681
Natalie even got suspended
from school.

20:45.781 --> 20:47.519
- Suspended?

20:47.619 --> 20:49.877
Is she okay?
- Yeah.

20:51.026 --> 20:52.940
No.

20:53.246 --> 20:54.601
My mom and her are
down each other's throats

20:54.701 --> 20:56.132
about the whole Amy thing.

20:56.232 --> 20:58.199
- Well, I'm glad
they finally know.

20:58.299 --> 21:00.213
- What--wait.

21:00.826 --> 21:02.065
When did you know?

21:02.165 --> 21:04.079
- Oh.
[chuckles]

21:06.989 --> 21:09.990
About a year ago,
she was really freaked out,

21:10.090 --> 21:11.904
and I asked her why,
and she said

21:12.004 --> 21:13.358
she thought she was
going to hell.

21:13.458 --> 21:14.354
- Why didn't you tell me?
- I wanted to.

21:14.454 --> 21:16.650
But I promised her I wouldn't.

21:16.750 --> 21:19.521
She's like a little sister
to me.

21:19.621 --> 21:22.622
I know you guys
never got that, but...

21:22.722 --> 21:24.498
I really did consider
you family.

21:24.598 --> 21:27.216
- I always knew that...

21:27.316 --> 21:29.436
and I appreciated it.

21:29.536 --> 21:31.450
- Thank you.

21:33.096 --> 21:34.872
- Are you hungry?
- Mm.

21:34.972 --> 21:36.480
- Come on.

21:36.580 --> 21:38.317
Let me buy you lunch
as a thank you

21:38.417 --> 21:40.959
for saving me from prison.
- [chuckles]

21:41.059 --> 21:42.973
Okay.

21:44.734 --> 21:45.935
[pop music playing]

21:46.035 --> 21:47.773
- It's like--do I even look
at these messages

21:47.873 --> 21:49.572
or do I just ignore them?

21:49.672 --> 21:51.601
- Will you enjoy the show more

21:51.701 --> 21:53.362
knowing what they say
or not knowing?

21:53.462 --> 21:55.544
♪ ♪

21:55.644 --> 21:56.769
- I have to look.

21:56.869 --> 21:58.300
Otherwise, my mind
will just torture me.

21:58.400 --> 22:00.520
♪ ♪

22:00.620 --> 22:02.702
My God, Daniel was arrested.

22:02.802 --> 22:04.616
- What?

22:04.716 --> 22:06.630
- I don't know, but...

22:08.889 --> 22:11.430
Amy, I'm having the best time
of my life, seriously--

22:11.530 --> 22:14.033
- But he's your brother,
and you wanna go home.

22:14.133 --> 22:15.450
♪ ♪

22:15.550 --> 22:16.407
Come on.

22:16.507 --> 22:17.861
♪ ♪

22:17.961 --> 22:20.044
- Do you hate me?
- No, I--of course not.

22:20.144 --> 22:21.422
I don't hate you.

22:21.522 --> 22:22.953
♪ ♪

22:23.053 --> 22:24.943
In fact, the opposite.

22:25.043 --> 22:26.551
♪ ♪

22:26.651 --> 22:27.776
I love you.

22:27.876 --> 22:30.954
♪ ♪

22:31.054 --> 22:34.054
Come on, let's hit the road
before traffic gets bad.

22:34.154 --> 22:35.586
- Oh, okay.

22:35.686 --> 22:38.648
♪ ♪

22:38.748 --> 22:41.672
[soft jazz music playing]

22:41.772 --> 22:44.964
[indistinct chatter]

22:45.064 --> 22:47.208
- Scotch, neat please.

22:50.041 --> 22:50.936
Lewis.

22:51.036 --> 22:52.735
- [sighs]

22:52.835 --> 22:54.749
Thanks for coming.

22:57.046 --> 22:59.243
- I assume from the deference
in your tone,

22:59.343 --> 23:01.425
you realize I've already won.

23:01.525 --> 23:03.439
Thank you.

23:06.081 --> 23:09.258
- I have cancer, Gideon--
prostate.

23:11.363 --> 23:13.277
Noa doesn't know.

23:14.655 --> 23:17.259
We think we caught it early,
but...

23:21.546 --> 23:23.460
- I'm sorry to hear that.

23:26.905 --> 23:29.217
- The differences
between you and me

23:29.317 --> 23:31.231
could fill a stadium...

23:33.222 --> 23:35.136
But we have one thing
in common.

23:36.973 --> 23:41.084
I said before that she believes
there's humanity in you.

23:41.184 --> 23:43.228
I'm rolling the dice
that she's right.

23:43.328 --> 23:44.606
- [sighs]

23:44.706 --> 23:46.620
So what are you proposing?

23:48.075 --> 23:49.468
- Come on, Gideon.

23:49.568 --> 23:52.071
You don't wanna run Noa Corp.

23:52.171 --> 23:54.085
What is this all
really about, anyway?

24:00.631 --> 24:01.909
- [sighs]

24:02.009 --> 24:04.091
Regulators in Singapore
have frozen construction

24:04.191 --> 24:05.852
of my new high-rise.

24:05.952 --> 24:08.417
I'm having a hard time
finding banks

24:08.517 --> 24:13.163
who are willing to fund me
on a short-term cash basis.

24:13.263 --> 24:15.805
I'm facing losses.
You know my motto.

24:15.905 --> 24:17.642
- "Never a loss
in any quarter."

24:17.742 --> 24:20.781
- I'll name Mark Logan as CEO,
and in return,

24:20.881 --> 24:24.035
he's agreed to let me
use the Noa Corp balance sheet

24:24.135 --> 24:26.562
to guarantee my debt.

24:26.662 --> 24:28.576
- Why make a deal with him?

24:30.145 --> 24:32.059
Make a deal with me.

24:33.399 --> 24:35.313
- Lewis...

24:36.194 --> 24:38.644
I already hold
the winning hand.

24:40.672 --> 24:42.869
- But at what price?

24:42.969 --> 24:45.894
[soft dramatic music]

24:45.994 --> 24:52.540
♪ ♪

25:10.225 --> 25:13.953
- Having reflected
on my daughter's words earlier,

25:14.053 --> 25:17.399
I do believe that she has
awakened to the neglect

25:17.499 --> 25:19.734
that these outside distractions
have caused.

25:19.834 --> 25:22.222
♪ ♪

25:22.322 --> 25:25.285
I would like
to withdraw my motion

25:25.385 --> 25:28.079
and suggest that she should,
in fact,

25:28.179 --> 25:30.567
remain in control
of her own company.

25:30.667 --> 25:34.740
♪ ♪

25:34.840 --> 25:36.754
- Oh, my God.
- Lewis!

25:50.726 --> 25:52.640
- Fancy meeting you here.

25:53.751 --> 25:56.215
- You know, you'd already
won the board over, right?

25:56.315 --> 25:58.436
You didn't need to pass out.

25:58.536 --> 26:01.766
- Well, you know me.

26:01.866 --> 26:03.780
Leave everything
on the table....

26:04.967 --> 26:06.513
Or, in my case,
under the table.

26:06.613 --> 26:09.675
- [laughing]

26:11.283 --> 26:13.097
[indistinct PA announcements]

26:13.197 --> 26:15.877
The doctor says you passed out
because of the flu.

26:18.250 --> 26:20.945
He says that's common
in cancer patients.

26:21.045 --> 26:24.582
[soft dramatic music]

26:24.682 --> 26:26.596
- I was gonna tell you.

26:27.782 --> 26:29.673
- You didn't think
I could handle it?

26:29.773 --> 26:32.046
- No, it's not that.

26:32.146 --> 26:34.420
We were in a street fight.

26:34.520 --> 26:36.410
Your father
was gunning for you.

26:36.510 --> 26:37.406
- Lewis--

26:37.506 --> 26:40.621
- No, don't say
that's not important.

26:40.721 --> 26:44.564
To be as influential
and meaningful as you are, Noa,

26:44.664 --> 26:47.703
that is everything
that I've devoted my life

26:47.803 --> 26:48.775
to helping you become.

26:48.875 --> 26:51.148
- Yes, I know,
and I've appreciated

26:51.248 --> 26:53.943
every minute of that effort,

26:54.043 --> 26:56.316
but no company or fight

26:56.416 --> 26:59.379
are a shadow
of what you mean to me.

26:59.479 --> 27:01.393
- I know.

27:02.235 --> 27:04.279
- [softly] Okay.
[laughs]

27:04.379 --> 27:06.690
♪ ♪

27:06.790 --> 27:09.868
- Besides...
I'm gonna be just fine.

27:09.968 --> 27:11.782
- Yes, you are.

27:11.882 --> 27:15.954
♪ ♪

27:16.054 --> 27:18.060
- Are you sure?
- Yes, I'm sure.

27:18.160 --> 27:19.629
Do you know why?

27:19.729 --> 27:22.768
Because as of now, you're
gonna let me take care of you.

27:22.868 --> 27:27.286
- Well, don't go overboard.

27:27.386 --> 27:28.511
- I'm sorry,
but you have no choice.

27:28.611 --> 27:30.616
The company's safe.

27:30.716 --> 27:31.956
Besides, I'm looking forward

27:32.056 --> 27:34.023
to bossing you around
for a change.

27:34.123 --> 27:39.574
♪ ♪

27:39.674 --> 27:42.942
[upbeat music playing
over speakers]

27:43.042 --> 27:44.742
- Mmm.
- Good, right?

27:44.842 --> 27:46.349
- So good.
- Mm.

27:46.449 --> 27:47.919
- Did you know this place?
- Nope.

27:48.019 --> 27:49.680
That's one of the great things
about Miami--

27:49.780 --> 27:51.249
surprises everywhere you go.

27:51.349 --> 27:55.231
♪ ♪

27:55.331 --> 27:57.642
- I like your videos.

27:57.742 --> 27:59.288
I mean, the first one
at Piñones--

27:59.388 --> 28:00.781
If I never see that again,
it would be okay.

28:00.881 --> 28:02.159
- [chuckles]

28:02.259 --> 28:04.495
- But the second one
with Betsi...

28:04.595 --> 28:06.945
It was really good.

28:07.045 --> 28:09.088
- Thank you.

28:09.188 --> 28:11.538
- Mateo said you might try
doing it as your career?

28:11.638 --> 28:12.916
- He did?

28:13.016 --> 28:14.869
♪ ♪

28:14.969 --> 28:16.362
I don't know.

28:16.462 --> 28:17.548
My parents think it's stupid.

28:17.648 --> 28:20.190
- You can't listen
to them, Daniel.

28:20.290 --> 28:21.874
I always appreciate
their point of view,

28:21.974 --> 28:23.712
but I always thought you were
meant for more than the bakery.

28:23.812 --> 28:25.358
- You did?

28:25.458 --> 28:27.348
- I only said that to you,
like, a million times.

28:27.448 --> 28:30.411
Did you ever listen to me?
- I did.

28:30.511 --> 28:33.282
I just thought you were saying
that because, you know,

28:33.382 --> 28:35.234
we were together,
and you felt like you had to.

28:35.334 --> 28:36.880
- Okay, first of all,
I never said anything

28:36.980 --> 28:38.105
just because
we were together,

28:38.205 --> 28:40.134
and, second of all,
me doing something

28:40.234 --> 28:42.354
because I felt like I had to?
- [chuckles]

28:42.454 --> 28:44.881
- Do you know me?
- [laughs]

28:44.981 --> 28:47.178
No, fair enough, fair enough.

28:47.278 --> 28:50.814
♪ ♪

28:50.914 --> 28:52.499
- [sighs]

28:52.599 --> 28:54.451
This is nice.

28:54.551 --> 28:55.906
Right?

28:56.006 --> 28:58.317
- Don't act surprised.

28:58.417 --> 29:02.260
It's not like we had
four miserable years together.

29:02.360 --> 29:05.323
- No, there was a lot
that was good.

29:05.423 --> 29:07.811
[tender acoustic music]

29:07.911 --> 29:09.342
- It's nice to hear
you say that.

29:09.442 --> 29:11.295
♪ ♪

29:11.395 --> 29:13.056
I mean, I know Noa Hamilton
is not the reason

29:13.156 --> 29:15.773
why you turned me down...

29:15.873 --> 29:19.525
And I know she isn't really
the reason why we broke up...

29:19.625 --> 29:20.827
But it's nice to hear you say

29:20.927 --> 29:23.544
you don't think
those four years were wasted.

29:23.644 --> 29:26.607
- V, I'll never think that.

29:26.707 --> 29:28.980
♪ ♪

29:29.080 --> 29:31.660
Okay?

29:31.760 --> 29:32.770
[chuckles]

29:32.870 --> 29:37.708
♪ ♪

29:37.808 --> 29:39.354
Maybe I should get the check.
- I should get the car in.

29:39.454 --> 29:44.484
♪ ♪

29:44.584 --> 29:47.379
[thunder rumbling]

29:52.968 --> 29:55.586
- This day started off so bad.

29:55.686 --> 29:57.921
You really came through for me.

29:58.021 --> 29:59.643
♪ ♪

29:59.743 --> 30:01.657
- Who is that?

30:03.533 --> 30:05.562
- I think that's Natalie
and Amy.

30:09.122 --> 30:12.491
- Dude, I'm telling you
that's Daniel in Vanessa's car.

30:14.022 --> 30:16.817
- But why?
- I don't know.

30:20.568 --> 30:22.482
- I should get going.
- Yeah.

30:24.013 --> 30:25.904
- I would say "say hi
to your parents for me," but...

30:26.004 --> 30:27.918
you know.

30:28.645 --> 30:30.995
- Hey, my dad always loved you.

30:31.095 --> 30:32.718
- As opposed to your mom.

30:32.818 --> 30:36.316
- You know Cuban mothers.
No one's ever good enough.

30:36.416 --> 30:39.417
- Hmm. Not even Noa Hamilton?

30:39.517 --> 30:42.480
- Let's just say she's not high
on anyone's list right now.

30:42.580 --> 30:44.494
- Oh.

30:45.680 --> 30:47.594
Well, I'm sorry to hear that.

30:48.896 --> 30:50.810
Sort of.

30:51.652 --> 30:54.155
- Good night.
- Good night.

30:54.255 --> 30:56.835
[soft music]

30:56.935 --> 30:59.515
♪ ♪

30:59.615 --> 31:02.654
- Actually, can I ask you
for one more favor?

31:02.754 --> 31:04.912
♪ ♪

31:05.012 --> 31:07.194
- Time to face the salsa music.

31:08.496 --> 31:10.080
- Any regrets?

31:10.180 --> 31:12.224
- That I didn't do
something like this sooner.

31:12.324 --> 31:19.023
♪ ♪

31:20.057 --> 31:23.785
Also...I love you too.

31:23.885 --> 31:29.206
♪ ♪

31:30.545 --> 31:31.938
- [gasps]

31:32.038 --> 31:34.580
Ay, thank God you're home.

31:34.680 --> 31:37.719
Oh, my baby.
Where were you?

31:37.819 --> 31:39.403
- We hit a couple obstacles,
but we're good.

31:39.503 --> 31:41.417
- Mm.

31:41.838 --> 31:44.227
- The point is that you're out,
and this nightmare is over.

31:44.327 --> 31:45.222
- Yes.
- You okay?

31:45.322 --> 31:47.236
- Yeah.

31:51.677 --> 31:53.591
- How was school?

32:10.204 --> 32:12.172
- Vanessa,
what are you doing here?

32:12.272 --> 32:13.397
- The real question is,
what are you doing

32:13.497 --> 32:14.698
taking apart this room?

32:14.798 --> 32:18.335
You have a song to write--
a follow-up to "Calle Ocho."

32:18.435 --> 32:20.057
- Vanessa, I told you
it's over.

32:20.157 --> 32:22.814
- I don't care what you said.
You are a temperamental artist.

32:22.914 --> 32:24.651
I'm the one
with her head on straight.

32:24.751 --> 32:27.484
- Vanessa--
- Mateo, you owe me.

32:27.584 --> 32:29.283
Put these back on.
- I can't.

32:29.383 --> 32:30.967
- Sure you can.

32:31.067 --> 32:31.963
- Just stop it.
- Not a chance.

32:32.063 --> 32:33.685
- No.
- Yes.

32:33.785 --> 32:40.561
♪ ♪

33:01.348 --> 33:03.430
[rain pattering]

33:03.530 --> 33:05.152
- Mom, I really
don't want to fight.

33:05.252 --> 33:06.339
- Natalie--
- And I know everything

33:06.439 --> 33:07.602
about my appearance
says otherwise,

33:07.702 --> 33:08.827
and I'm sorry...
- Natalie--

33:08.927 --> 33:10.244
- That I cut school, okay?

33:10.344 --> 33:11.660
But for the first time
in my life, I'm just happy

33:11.760 --> 33:13.674
for the first time--
- Natalie Garcia, stop.

33:15.741 --> 33:17.655
[sighs]

33:18.306 --> 33:21.728
I know you think
I've been overreacting,

33:21.828 --> 33:24.967
but you have to understand--
you're my daughter.

33:31.283 --> 33:36.198
I know I've told you how close
I was to your grandmother...

33:36.298 --> 33:38.303
but what I didn't tell you
was that before she died,

33:38.403 --> 33:40.432
we got into a terrible fight...

33:43.533 --> 33:45.347
[breathing shakily,
voice breaking]

33:45.447 --> 33:47.989
And the last thing
I said to her

33:48.089 --> 33:52.529
was that...
she meant nothing to me...

33:54.520 --> 33:56.793
And that she wasn't
even my mother.

33:56.893 --> 33:58.516
[exhales]

33:58.616 --> 34:01.923
And so when I had you,
I swore I would never let

34:02.023 --> 34:05.138
anything come between us.

34:05.238 --> 34:11.684
But then, you were so smart
and talented,

34:11.784 --> 34:15.689
and I thought, "What do I have
to offer this girl?"

34:17.450 --> 34:21.469
And then I thought, "At least
I can help her navigate love."

34:23.919 --> 34:25.542
But then you fell
in love with Amy.

34:25.642 --> 34:27.556
[laughs]

34:28.360 --> 34:30.633
And I overreacted,

34:30.733 --> 34:34.332
and I pushed you away.

34:36.437 --> 34:39.783
And here I have this amazing,

34:39.883 --> 34:42.922
beautiful girl

34:43.022 --> 34:45.525
who must look at me
and say,

34:45.625 --> 34:48.281
"I have nothing
in common with her.

34:48.381 --> 34:50.157
I'm nothing like her."

34:50.257 --> 34:52.568
- Mom, no.

34:52.668 --> 34:54.750
Okay, sure, there are
a lot of ways

34:54.850 --> 34:59.000
that we're not too similar,
but all of the good parts

34:59.100 --> 35:00.684
about me are from you.

35:00.784 --> 35:02.407
- [chuckles softly]
- Okay?

35:02.507 --> 35:04.933
Just don't tell Dad that.
- [chuckles]

35:05.033 --> 35:08.685
- But I look at other kids,
and I think how lucky I am

35:08.785 --> 35:10.024
that you're my mom.

35:10.124 --> 35:11.249
- [sighs]

35:11.349 --> 35:13.087
[soft music]

35:13.187 --> 35:15.384
- Thank you, baby.

35:15.484 --> 35:19.901
♪ ♪

35:20.001 --> 35:22.351
And I don't think you should
stop seeing Amy

35:22.451 --> 35:24.763
if she makes you happy.

35:24.863 --> 35:27.059
♪ ♪

35:27.159 --> 35:28.935
Yeah.
- Thank you, Mom.

35:29.035 --> 35:30.849
- [laughs] Of course.
- Thank you.

35:30.949 --> 35:33.682
♪ ♪

35:33.782 --> 35:38.391
- But you're still grounded
for cutting school,

35:38.491 --> 35:41.721
and don't think
I'm gonna be soft on you

35:41.821 --> 35:42.984
because we've had
this little chat.

35:43.084 --> 35:44.898
- Oh, I know.

35:44.998 --> 35:47.272
- I have to.
[laughs]

35:47.372 --> 35:49.860
I love you.
[sniffling]

35:52.540 --> 35:54.507
- I've arranged
for the financing.

35:54.607 --> 35:57.072
It's contingent on you
resigning from my board,

35:57.172 --> 35:58.526
but you shouldn't have
any more problems

35:58.626 --> 36:01.014
or incur any losses.

36:01.114 --> 36:03.029
- And so we both win.

36:05.249 --> 36:08.556
- Were you really gonna
put Mark Logan in charge

36:08.656 --> 36:11.144
Or did you design this
whole thing to force my hand?

36:14.130 --> 36:15.867
- I designed it so
we'd never have to find out

36:15.967 --> 36:17.475
the answer to that question.

36:17.575 --> 36:19.489
- [chuckles]

36:21.097 --> 36:24.810
Can't things just be simple
between us, Dad?

36:26.265 --> 36:27.811
Why didn't you just
ask for help?

36:27.911 --> 36:30.284
- Bug, everyone parents
in their own way.

36:31.663 --> 36:34.204
And I think, one day,

36:34.304 --> 36:36.984
you'll appreciate the way I am.

36:41.654 --> 36:43.353
And, in any case,
at least I knew enough

36:43.453 --> 36:44.693
to get the hell
out of your life

36:44.793 --> 36:46.645
and let Lewis take care of you.

36:46.745 --> 36:48.812
- Don't you dare
compare yourself to him.

37:00.679 --> 37:02.670
- I'll see you soon, Bug.

37:05.197 --> 37:08.795
[cell phone buzzing]

37:14.001 --> 37:15.915
- Hello, Daniel?

37:16.872 --> 37:18.786
Where are you?

37:20.050 --> 37:22.821
Uh, stay there.
I can come to you.

37:22.921 --> 37:29.620
♪ ♪

37:34.175 --> 37:35.492
[phone ringing]

37:35.592 --> 37:37.827
- Noa, are you okay?
How'd it go?

37:37.927 --> 37:39.511
- Oh, my God.
You should have seen him.

37:39.611 --> 37:42.229
He showed no remorse,
no consideration

37:42.329 --> 37:43.799
for what
he just put me through.

37:43.899 --> 37:47.435
- Honey, I'm so sorry,
but why am I not surprised?

37:47.535 --> 37:49.885
- It's like--he gets himself
into trouble,

37:49.985 --> 37:52.412
concocts this crazy plan
for me to help him,

37:52.512 --> 37:54.555
and then he acts
like he's doing me a favor?

37:54.655 --> 37:57.005
It took all my willpower
not to make a scene in there.

37:57.105 --> 37:58.766
- Well, then,
damn your willpower

37:58.866 --> 38:00.642
because I would've paid
cash money to see you do that.

38:00.742 --> 38:02.633
- Yeah, but that's
what he would've wanted.

38:02.733 --> 38:04.355
[sighs]

38:04.455 --> 38:07.609
And I'm better than that
because you raised me.

38:07.709 --> 38:10.633
♪ ♪

38:10.733 --> 38:13.619
And I'm much more your daughter
than I am his.

38:13.719 --> 38:18.213
♪ ♪

38:18.313 --> 38:19.783
- Which is why I'm gonna ask
you to bring your old man

38:19.883 --> 38:22.615
some penne pomodoro
from Lordo's, okay?

38:22.715 --> 38:25.907
'Cause the food here sucks.
- Sure.

38:26.007 --> 38:27.630
♪ ♪

38:27.730 --> 38:28.970
[sighs]

38:29.070 --> 38:31.573
♪ ♪

38:31.673 --> 38:34.521
First I gotta go see Daniel.

38:34.621 --> 38:36.856
- You wanna talk about it?
- What's there to talk about?

38:36.956 --> 38:40.263
You were sick,
and I didn't even notice,

38:40.363 --> 38:43.708
so...that tells me everything
I need to know.

38:43.808 --> 38:46.579
[tender Latin pop music]

38:46.679 --> 38:53.187
♪ ♪

38:54.871 --> 38:57.551
- [singing in Spanish]

38:59.044 --> 39:00.628
- Hey.
- Hi.

39:00.728 --> 39:01.738
♪ ♪

39:01.838 --> 39:03.997
- What happened
with the board members?

39:04.097 --> 39:05.796
- I won.

39:05.896 --> 39:07.480
- I told you
it was gonna work out.

39:07.580 --> 39:09.356
- Yeah.
- [laughs]

39:09.456 --> 39:11.041
- I've been trying
to reach you all day.

39:11.141 --> 39:12.419
♪ ♪

39:12.519 --> 39:14.562
- [sighs]
I was in jail.

39:14.662 --> 39:15.519
It's a long story.

39:15.619 --> 39:16.591
I don't even know
where to begin.

39:16.691 --> 39:19.424
- Don't.
- What?

39:19.524 --> 39:25.894
♪ ♪

39:25.994 --> 39:28.956
I think we need to stop
seeing each other, Daniel.

39:29.056 --> 39:31.023
♪ ♪

39:31.123 --> 39:32.440
- How can you just say that?

39:32.540 --> 39:35.081
- Daniel, when two people
are right for each other,

39:35.181 --> 39:38.258
they make each other's
lives better,

39:38.358 --> 39:41.895
and since we've been together,
your family's fighting,

39:41.995 --> 39:45.072
the bakery's in trouble,
you got arrested,

39:45.172 --> 39:47.178
I almost lost my company.

39:47.278 --> 39:49.168
♪ ♪

39:49.268 --> 39:51.848
It's like--how many more people

39:51.948 --> 39:55.753
are gonna have to get hurt
before we get the message?

39:55.853 --> 39:57.514
♪ ♪

39:57.614 --> 39:59.619
Oh.

39:59.719 --> 40:03.256
♪ ♪

40:03.356 --> 40:05.974
- So that's it?

40:06.074 --> 40:07.849
One bad week and it's over.

40:07.949 --> 40:12.673
- If I were anyone else, no,
but I'm not, Daniel.

40:12.773 --> 40:15.123
♪ ♪

40:15.223 --> 40:18.491
- It's so funny you said that.

40:18.591 --> 40:21.516
In all the time
I've known you...

40:21.616 --> 40:25.076
This is the first time
you look ordinary to me.

40:25.176 --> 40:31.683
♪ ♪
